PROCESS FOR SUBMODULING FOLDER/FILES

Steps to add submodules:
1) fork qa_common
2) clone qa_common locally
3) unify files across different projects into qa_common
4) PR and merge changes into qa_common
5) Delete corresponding folders in porjects
6) CD into project 
7) git submodule add https://github.com/TIES-Software/qa_common common


When commiting changes:
git push <branch>
git push --recurse-submodules
OR add this to make sure you never forget to commit changes to submodules: 
git config push.recurseSubmodules on-demand


When pulling down changes: 
git pull upstream <branch>
git pull --recurse-submodules 


MORE RESCOURCES ABOUT SUBMODULES:
https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Tools-Submodules

Troubleshoot:
if you run into: fatal: Pathspec '<file>' is in submodule '<path>' when adding commits.
git rm -rf --cached <path>/
git add <path>/
then try commiting
